>    AFAIK, Linux is the *first* OS that started out as a kernel only. All
>    of the userland was added.
>
>What you're calling "userland" is practically the whole operating
>system--and it happens to be the GNU operating system.  Linux, the
No, Linux the Kernel *is* Linux the operating system. The only GNU
operating system is HURD.
If you like we could agree that a GNU/Linux System is one that includes
GNU utilities running on a Linux Operating System. 
I doubt if people will actually start saying that instead of just Linux or
RedHat or Debian or... , but at least it is a more correct description
than calling a distribution an operating system.
